Switzerland’s Government May Bring Forward Franc News Briefing

-- B y   K l a u s   W i l l e
-- 
2011-08-16T16:25:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/switzerland-s-government-may-bring-forward-franc-news-briefing.html
Switzerland ’s federal council will
decide tomorrow whether it will bring forward a news briefing on
the Swiss franc to tomorrow afternoon from Aug. 18, the
government said today in an e-mailed statement.  The government at its first regular meeting after the
summer recess will tomorrow morning discuss measures regarding
the franc’s strength, spokesman Andre Simonazzi told Bloomberg
News by phone. The briefing was originally scheduled for a day
later.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Klaus Wille in Zurich at 
 kwille@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
